claim.claim-text:
The occluding catheter (37) as set forth in claim 1, comprising a proximal occluding balloon (38) carried by the shaft (104), wherein the proximal occluding balloon (38) is inflated to occlude blood flow through one of the right carotid artery (26R) and the left carotid artery (26L); and

a distal occluding balloon (42) carried by the shaft (104), wherein the distal occluding balloon (42) is inflated to occlude blood flow through one of the right carotid artery (26R) and the left carotid artery (26L) that is not occluded by the proximal occluding balloon (38);

wherein the shaft (104) has a segment (44) that is located between the proximal occluding balloon (38) and the distal occluding balloon (42).
